   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR A VIEW OF GOD'S ECONOMY FROM THE NEW TESTAMENT REVELATION 2 Scripture Reading: Eph 3:2-11; 1:9-11 OUTLINE The ascended God-man as the Head in His ascension: Pouring out the Holy Spirit as the ultimate consummation of the Triune God, the realization and reality of Him as the Head, upon all His believers throughout all the ages and among all the nations Acts 2:1-4, 33.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Baptizing them into one Body, the church 1 Cor 12:13a.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The church being given to drink of Him as the Spirit and becoming one Spirit with Him 1 Cor 12:13b; 6:17: Enjoying His all-inclusive Spirit as the life supply Phil 1:19.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Receiving gifts from Him to function as members of His Body Rom 12:4-8.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The church as the Body of Christ being expressed as the local churches in all the localities to be the golden lampstands shining forth Christ Rev 1:11-12, 20b: In administrative affairs, being administered locally.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In life, nature, and testimony, being the unique Body of Christ in the whole universe Eph 4:3-6; 1 Cor 12:12.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Having the sevenfold intensified Spirit of Christ for the strengthening of the shining of the golden lampstands Rev 1:4; 4:5; 5:6.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The failure of the church: Becoming desolate and degraded Rev 2:14-15, 20.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Being carried away to the mysterious Great Babylon Rev 17:5.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The recovery of the church: Leaving the Great Babylon Rev 18:4.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Returning to the original ground of the church, recovering the normal church life Rev 3:1, 4, 7-12.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The overcomers in the church and the overcomers among the Old Testament saints eventually constituting: The bride of Christ Rev 19:7-9.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The army of Christ, with Christ defeating Antichrist and his army Rev 17:12-14; 19:19-20.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The New Jerusalem in the millennium, as the manifestation of the kingdom of the heavens, reigning with Christ to shepherd the nations Rev 3:12; 20:4, 6; 2:26-27.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>All the saints in the church and those in the Old Testament ultimately becoming the New Jerusalem in the new heaven and new earth Rev 21:1-2,12,14: As the mutual dwelling place for God and His redeemed in eternity Rev 21:3, 22.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>As the full expression of God for eternity Rev 21:10-11, 23-24.</S>
   </TEXT>
